#Explanation



- Subsequences of a string


Explanation:

Given a string, we have to find out all subsequences of it. A String is a subsequence of a given String,
that is generated by deleting some character of a given string without changing its order.





Example

Input :
str = "aba"


Output :

aba
ab
aa
a
ba
b
a



#Explanation END


package vaibhav;

public class Recursive_Subsequence {
	
	public static void subs(String str, int idx, String newString) {
		if(idx == str.length()) {
			System.out.println(newString);
			return;
		}
		
		char currChar = str.charAt(idx);
		
		// to be
		subs(str, idx+1, newString + currChar);
		
		// not to be
		subs(str, idx+1, newString);
		
	}

	public static void main(String[] args) {
		// TODO Auto-generated method stub
		String str = "aba";
		subs(str,0,"");
	}

}
